[The European Commission (EC) said Wednesday, 5 Apr 2006: "The authorities
of the United Kingdom have informed the European Commission that
preliminary tests have found the highly pathogenic avian influenza virus H5
in a sample from a dead wild swan detected in Cellardyke, Fife, Scotland".
